vacature tekst.251203-OF-006:
For Rabobank Utrecht we are looking for an Application Support Engineer

Important:
• Due to the large expected professionals for this position, we unfortunately can not provide substantive feedback for all rejected candidates;
• We are only looking for 1FTE. We will close the vacancy before the indicated deadline when we received enough professionals. Please upload you most suitable candidate as soon as possible;
• Suppliers can offer just one candidate for this position. Multiple candidates per supplier are not allowed, all candidates will be rejected.
• Language: English mandatory;
• ZZP Allowed: No.

Making a difference… 

The Application Support Officer is the expert in the field of SaaS application support of our HR products. As a member of the Application Support Chapter, it is your responsibility to provide a stable run and support on all SaaS applications within HR except from Workday. Being ‘in control’ is essential. It is a responsibility with impact, that you shape by resolving issues within your squad, chapter or in cooperation with the supplier. You are studious, and you are challenged by developing expertise on various applications in order to be able to exceed the expectations of your (internal) clients. 

Currently, some applications are being replaced and some added to continuously adapt to changing HR processes and IT landscape. Furthermore, the SaaS team has adopted the new way of working which is the standard within Rabobank. This way of working, called Simplified @ Scale, or S@S, focusses on simplification and acceleration of digitalisation within the bank. We do so by working in tribes, area’s, chapters and squads. 

The Application Support Engineer is willing to learn and adapt to this new way of working and at the same time, makes sure the application support continues as planned. In addition, responsibilities of the Application Support Officer include:  
• Incident- and problem management;
• IT In Control activities – keeping our recurring Security &amp; Risk assessments up to date, such as Security Assessment Questionnaires, Security Designs, Privacy Impact Assessments (DPIA) and more;
• Collaborating with a diverse and demanding field of IT- and (HR) business stakeholders to ensure high-end service and availability of HR systems; 
• Being a professional and reliable partner for system-, business- and process owners;
• Help to further build the application engineering chapter.


With each other 
As an Application Support Officer you become part of the team SaaS which is one of the teams within Global HR Systems (GHS). 

GHS is responsible for implementing the standards for the global HR Solutions way-of-working and data management, working with HR teams worldwide. Standards that aim for a world-class, agile professional HR organisation that delivers business value through standardisation, automation, increased forecasting capabilities and proactive handling of services: high tech, high touch. 

GHS is part of the HR domain. HR is the frontrunner in the field of the provision of SaaS applications to make sure we can optimally service our internal clients. Besides the diverse SaaS applications we support, the biggest cloud application is Workday, that we rolled out in 2019. 


With you 
Quality orientation, result orientation and pro-activity are clearly essential competences / characteristics for the role of Application Support Officer. In addition, it's important that you recognise yourself in the points below: 
• Bachelor Degree with 4-7 years of experience;
• Experience with application support on SaaS applications (experience in a similar role would be beneficial); 
• Experience with Security &amp; Risk assessments within the IT In Control process; 
• Affinity with HR technology and HR business processes;
• Experience with Learning applications or HR Learning domain is a plus; 
• Experience with agile way of working;
• Good command of English and Dutch speaking is required. 


The following Rabobank skills are required for this position: 
• Creativity; 
• Proactive; 
• Collaboration; 
• Agility; 
• Customer centric thinking.We would like to receive a motivation showing the required competencies. 

Additional information:
• All departments are working hybrid, in terms of Rabobank @anywhere policy;
• Suppliers must be aware of the laws and regulations regarding employment conditions and Rabobank’s Collective Labour Agreement. This assignment is placed in scale 9;
• We would like to receive the personal motivation of the candidate and CV in English;
• Due to changing laws and regulations, this assignment is NOT suitable for the deployment of a self-employed professional. Naturally, we are happy to answer any questions;
• A candidate should be submitted exclusively to Magnit – Rabobank during the exclusivity period of 4 business days on one request;
• Furthermore, the candidate has to be available throughout the entire duration of the assignment;
• All submitted candidates must be in possession of a valid Passport or ID card, which must be taken along to the interview and at the start of the assignment;
• Pre-employment screening: If the candidate is selected to start, a pre-employment screening will be executed. We will send you the required documents to be filled in and returned as soon as possible. Your candidate is only allowed to start after the pre-employment screening has been completed successfully;
• By submitting a candidate, you are agreeing to the terms of this specific client. If you are not familiar with these terms, you can ask our recruiters for a copy. 

IMPORTANT!: Complete all candidate details correctly. Enter the candidate's contact details under 'email address and telephone number'! The same applies to the address. This is information the client needs to receive with the submission. Incomplete/incorrect submissions risk being rejected.

vacature tekst.251203-OF-005:
For Rabobank Utrecht we are looking for a SharePoint Online Developer.

Important:
• Due to the large expected professionals for this position, we unfortunately can not provide substantive feedback for all rejected candidates;
• We are only looking for 1FTE. We will close the vacancy before the indicated deadline when we received enough professionals. Please upload you most suitable candidate as soon as possible;
• Suppliers can offer just one candidate for this position. Multiple candidates per supplier are not allowed, all candidates will be rejected.
• Language: English mandatory;
