About Us
Area Digital Workforce Dynamics (DWD) is committed to empowering productivity through seamless efficiency and innovation. We leverage Microsoft 365 (M365) as the backbone for internal communication and information services, ensuring Rabobank employees worldwide have access to personalized news, work instructions, and insights into internal and external developments. Our intranet serves as the formal content hub, while Viva Engage fosters informal collaboration and community building.

As part of our strategy, we are driving initiatives like the Employee Launchpad. A platform that brings HR, IT, and Facilities together in one intuitive workspace. It streamlines tasks, integrates multiple systems, and delivers personalized content to help employees work smarter and more efficiently. This supports our vision of a future-ready organization and an exceptional employee experience.
To ensure scalability and innovation, we build on SPFx, Azure, Power Automate, PowerShell, and other modern tools. Keeping our solutions robust and future-proof.

Role Overview
We are seeking a seasoned SharePoint Online Developer with strong front-end and back-end expertise to join our dynamic team. You will collaborate with a team consisting of a product owner, business analysts, implementation specialists, solution architect, and fellow engineers to unlock the full potential of Microsoft 365 and contribute to strategic initiatives like the Employee Launchpad.

Key Responsibilities
• Drive innovation and quality improvements across our SharePoint and M365 solutions;
• Lay the foundation for a scalable codebase supporting 100+ solutions;
• Oversee the lifecycle of building blocks such as SPFx solutions and Azure Functions;
• Promote code reuse, automation, and best practices for maintainability;
• Collaborate closely with the team to deliver impactful solutions aligned with DWD’s mission.

Key Qualifications
Must-Haves:
• Strong collaboration and communication skills;
• Expertise in SharePoint Online (Modern Pages) and SPFx framework;
• Proficiency in Azure platform, Power Automate, PowerShell, and Microsoft Graph API;
• Experience with JavaScript/React, PNP-JS, and C# for Azure Function Apps;
• Ability to oversee application lifecycles and adopt new technologies responsibly.We would like to receive a motivation showing the required competencies. 

