vacature tekst.251022-DT-001:
Client’s Inspector (electrical - instrumentation) 

PLEASE NOTE: Due to the international caracter of the rol, only freelancers (direct or offer through a supplier) are an option for this position! 

PLEASE NOTE: We no longer work with a ZZP Indirect construction within TenneT. This will be a fee-only construction (after 12 monthts, the fee only contract will end) where € 1,45 of the margin is retained from the supplier. 

About TenneT:
Europe's energy transition is among the greatest challenges of our time. Its goal: To make Europe the first climate-neutral continent by 2050 at the latest. The Netherlands and Germany have therefore set themselves ambitious goals to expand offshore wind energy: as early as 2030, Germany and the Netherlands want to reach a capacity of 30 and 22.2 Gigawatts, respectively. Energy from offshore wind farms in the European powerhouse North Sea will play in this a crucial role. TenneT guarantees that this energy will reach the mainland - and in the most environmentally friendly way possible. That is why we have developed the 2GW program with a unique transnational approach. And thus increase the pace and efficiency of the energy transition.

Unit Large Projects Offshore NL (LON):
Based on the Energy agreement, where the targets and intentions for the transition to a more renewable energy supply are set, the Roadmap Offshore wind energy 2030 and the ambition to realise additional windcapacity prior to 2030 a roll-out strategy is being prepared for the medium term, including the IJmuiden Ver (DC) projects. This results in a commitment for TenneT to realise at least 2x (with potential up to 5) 2GW HVDC Grid Connection Systems which bring the power from offshore wind-farms in the North sea to the Dutch electricity grid to be commissioned between 2028 - 2030.

Tasks
• Supports package lead (SPL) and QC coordinator with review all quality deliverables (as-built documents, punch lists, …) from the vendors against the Employer’s Requirements (subcontractors from the EPCI contractor);
•  Support the discipline: electrical/instrumentation and control/automation teams with specific quality related issues or documents;
• Monitors the execution of Inspection and Test Plans specified in the Inspection Notification from the EPCI Contractor for the vendor manufacturing phase;
• Witness inspection activities (electrical inspections, hardware and software tests, FATs) from client side for these vendor packages based on risk based inspection schedule;
• Frequent travelling to the vendor’s construction locations;
• Facilitates remote inspections by video connection (like Hololens) to TenneT office;
• Report and monitor all quality related problems for each package (NCR, open points);
• Monitor the implementation of Employer’s Requirements with regards to electrical/ instrumentation and control/automation equipment of vendor packages;
• Align with the TenneT QC coordinator about the inspections, ITPs and quality issues;
• Act in the role of Client (End-user, Employer) when witnessing tests and inspections.

Profile:
• Extensive experience with offshore projects in the Oil & Gas, Renewables or Shipping industry;
• Experience in reviewing and drafting QC plans and ITP’s;
• Minimum of 10 years of experience in QC inspection role;
• Knowledge of International Codes and Standards (i.e. BS/IEC/ISO/API/ATEX/EEMUA) relating to electrical and instrumentation work;
• Experience with variety of electrical, instrumentation and control/automation equipment inspections (a.o. switchgear, breakers, bushings, electric drives, automation systems);
• You are fluent in English, both verbally and in writing;
• Speaking Dutch is an advantage, but not mandatory.

Softskills:
• Good communication and interpersonal skills;
• You have problem solving skills – not only identify issues, but review supplier action / recovery plan as well;
• Ability to work independently and as part of a team (approx. 40-60% of the time in the office for review of vendor quality document, reports, etc.).

Conditions:
• At entry, TenneT performs a Pre-Employment Screening;
• Duty station for this position is Arnhem (two days a week), other days hybrid. You are willing to travel frequently internationally at locations in Europe (frequency and exact locations for now not known yet);
• Temporary position duo to the manufacturing phase (where inspections take place) for the duration of two year;
• In possession of driver license valid in NL / Europe;
• Candidate has to live in the Netherlands!


Additional information:
• Suppliers must be aware of the laws and regulations regarding employment conditions and Tennet’s Collective Labour Agreement. This assignment is placed in scale 8;
• We would like to receive the personal motivation of the candidate and CV in Dutch or English.

Screening:
• Pre-employment screening: If the candidate is selected to start, a pre-employment screening will be executed. We will send you the required documents to be filled in and returned as soon as possible. Your candidate is only allowed to start after the pre-employment screening has been completed successfully. The VOG Application is part of the screening. The VOG must be received before the candidate could start;
• All submitted candidates must be in possession of a valid Passport or ID card, which must be taken along to the interview and at the start of the assignment.

Availability: 
• Important, the candidate has to be available throughout the entire duration of the assignment;
• By submitting a candidate, you are agreeing to the terms of this specific client. If you are not familiar with these terms, you can ask our recruiters for a copy.
